OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FThe ombudsman investigated after a
OL,7,Fcomplaint was made by the child's
OL,8,Fmother.
OL,10,FHer son, who is non-verbal but can
OL,11,Fwalk unaided, used a special chair at
OL,12,Fmealtimes.
OL,14,FThe report said when the school
OL,15,Fclaimed it was having difficulty
OL,16,Fmoving him to the dining room it asked
OL,17,Fthe trust to add a wheeled base to the
OL,18,Fchair.
