OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FHis mother said this was unnecessary
OL,7,Frestraint, as he was able to walk but
OL,8,Fjust needed time and encouragement to
OL,9,Fdo so.
OL,11,FThe report said that when the trust
OL,12,Fwas told about the issues with the
OL,13,Fchild's mobility, the occupational
OL,14,Ftherapy team should have carried out a
OL,15,Fmulti-disciplinary assessment.
OL,17,FIt concluded that in approving and
OL,18,Ffitting the wheeled base to the chair,
OL,19,Fthe trust did not fully consider the
OL,20,Fchild's human rights.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
