OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,FThe investigation found that there was
OL,7,Fno assessment by the trust of the
OL,8,Fchild's needs prior to this change,
OL,9,Fand no assessment of whether he could
OL,10,Fengage in school activities with or
OL,11,Fwithout the chair.
OL,13,FThe report concluded that the chair
OL,14,Fwas an over prescription and caused
OL,15,Fhim to be restrained unnecessarily.
OL,17,FDeputy Ombudsman Sean Martin said:
OL,18,F"The failures in this case caused the
OL,19,Fchild's parents a huge amount of
OL,20,Fdistress.
