OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F442A1729688901
OL,3,CChild 'unnecessarily restrained' after
OL,4,Ctrust failed to monitor use of seating
OL,6,F"Our investigation highlights the
OL,7,Frequirement for health professionals
OL,8,Fto involve patients, or in this case
OL,9,Fparents, and work closely with others,
OL,10,Fparticularly schools before making
OL,11,Fdecisions on appropriate equipment for
OL,12,Fuse in a school setting.
OL,14,F"The trust should have given guidance
OL,15,Fto the school on how to use the
OL,16,Fspecialist chairs so that the child
OL,17,Fwas only restrained when it was
OL,18,Fabsolutely necessary.
