OL,6,F"The principle of using the least
OL,7,Frestraint possible should be an
OL,8,Fimperative for everyone, regardless of
OL,9,Fthe setting."
OL,11,FThe report welcomed the learning and
OL,12,Fservice improvements the trust has
OL,13,Fimplemented in response to the
OL,14,Fcomplaint.
OL,16,FIt said these include holding regular
OL,17,Fmultidisciplinary meetings to discuss
OL,18,Fany issues with restrictive practices,
OL,19,Fand the removal of belts from certain
OL,20,Fchairs within educational settings.
